    <p>This pup­petry per­for­mance is based on a clas­sic Chi­nese folk­tale about poor or­phan boy Ma Liang who was be­stowed by the gods a mag­i­cal paint­brush that brought ev­ery­thing he drew to life. This adap­ta­tion by Paper Mon­key Theatre was pre­sented at Moon­fest – A Mid-Au­tumn Cel­e­bra­tion 2017. Rec­om­mended for chil­dren aged five and above.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Es­planade Of­fs­tage</p>
    <p>WHEN: Pre­mieres tomorrow, 3pm (avail­able on Es­planade Of­fs­tage & Face­book af­ter pre­miere till Oct 4) AD­MIS­SION: Free INFO: str.sg/JBZY</p>


